When exporting to PDF or HTML links between pages of the space being exported are not fixed up but point back to the original space rather than linking to the page in the exported content.

Another way to describe this is:  if a space has page A and page B and A has a link to page B.  Then export pages A and B.  Let's call the exported pages XA and XB.  The link that is not in XA should point to XB but it points back to B.  This doesn't allow the content to be used offline.

