Some templates/blueprints are focused on particular activities, such as the Meeting Notes template. Restricting templates on a space level can be an insufficient level of control. 

For example, if a space is set up for a team, then it will contain a range of different pages, in which all templates are not required. Allowing a parent page to restrict the templates available to any children created underneath it would avoid the problem of being overwhelmed by too many templates.

